# Eaton LightScaping project

## Stack

- **Vite 8** — dev server and production build (`npm run dev`, `npm run build`).
- **Local dev**: `npm run dev` serves the site with **hot module reload** — changes to [`index.html`](index.html), [`src/style.css`](src/style.css), and [`src/main.js`](src/main.js) show up in the browser **without** running `npm run build`. Use **`npm run build`** when you need the **`dist/`** output (production bundle, GitHub Pages, or `npm run preview`).
- **Vanilla** single-page site: [`index.html`](index.html) (all sections), [`src/main.js`](src/main.js) (mobile nav), [`src/style.css`](src/style.css) (global styles).
- **Static assets** in [`public/`](public/) (e.g. favicon).
- **GitHub Pages**: production asset base is set in [`vite.config.js`](vite.config.js) (currently `/Eaton-Lighting/`). It must match the GitHub **repository name** used for Pages. Remote: [github.com/Nkizzy/Eaton-Lighting](https://github.com/Nkizzy/Eaton-Lighting).

