## Conventions

- Prefer updating **both** `index.html` and `src/style.css` when changing hero/section imagery (hero background lives in CSS).
- Keep **accessibility**: skip link, nav `aria-*`, meaningful `alt` on images, descriptive `title` on the map iframe. External Unsplash images use `referrerpolicy="no-referrer"` where applicable.
- Imagery is **placeholder** (Unsplash); client may supply real photos later.

## Mobile

- The site must **work well on mobile**: test layouts at narrow widths (e.g. ≤390px), keep tap targets adequate (`--tap-min`), and ensure the mobile nav, grids, and embeds do not overflow horizontally.
- **Gallery “compact” mode** uses `max-width: 56rem` — the same band as the sticky nav hamburger — so resizing a desktop window until the menu collapses matches the **two-column, caption-hidden** gallery used on phones.
- When changing layout or new sections, verify **small screens** alongside desktop; adjust breakpoints in [`src/style.css`](src/style.css) if something breaks.

